title: Israeli fire kills 2 Palestinian teens in Gaza clashes: Medics - Region - World
text:
Related Israeli fire kills six Palestinians in clashes on Gaza border PHOTO GALLERY: Israeli police clashes with Palestinians in Gaza Two Palestinian teens were killed and eight people wounded by Israeli fire during clashes Saturday at the Gaza border fence, emergency medical services in the coastal enclave said.
Marwan Darbakh, 13, and an unnamed 15-year-old were killed east of Khan Yunis in southern Gaza.
The deaths come a day after similar clashes killed seven Palestinians and wounded 145 in the bloodiest unrest in the territory since the summer 2014 assault on Gaza.
